The food is really good and the service, excellent.  The ambience just feels like another sports bar, but perfectly fine if that's what you're looking for.

This place was so lit! I took my girl yesterday for some last minute brunch and it was yet another perfect Brooklyn meal. Not one but both servers that worked during that shift helped us while serving almost 8 other parties so they’re really pro at their job. The environment is dope not too big but definitely worth the experience. The beer cheese dip is wild! Can’t wait to visit again sometime as it gets warmer. They said they’ll have a more spread out brunch menu soon but the lunch/dinner is their forte for the moment. Surprisingly they didn’t close because of Covid but for few minor issues outta their control other than that they are an elite ale house. If you want an awesome drink or bite most definitely try this spot. #SupportYourLocalBusinesses

I absolutely love this place. And they are back open again. The wings are always delicious and hot. Try all the flavors you won't be disappointed. Lots of beers on tap and good vibes. The food is on point and they are always pleasant.  Def check it out

So happy that this place opened up right near me! It's a great vibe, a delicious menu (though not a ton of vegetarian options), and some great beer. Some outdoor space for warmer weather, and they've been doing a solid job of being safe and consistent with COVID. Take an afternoon and support this place!

Today I made an order of A salud two quesadillas and honey bbq wings. First and for most they were super late with my order it was suppose to arrive from 8 to 8:30 and then I called the driver and he told me they told him 15 minutes. Also A few minutes later I got a call from the restaurant owner that the restaurant was closed and they were delayed with orders and that they would send me a complimentary drink that was not good. He told me to give them 30minutes and I ended up receiving my order at 10pm and the food and the drinks were not good  Also I received and email of a refund of a part of my order that they didn’t make and which I was told nothing about on the call. Dont  order from here don’t waist your money.

Great inviting atmosphere that is surrounded by dark enigmatic niches and warm incandescent lighting, creating the perfect setting for any occasion. Friendly, talkative and talented bartender, proved to be an excellent mixologist, (laying down an exquisite martini), and was very pleasing to the eyes I might add!  If I am ever in New York again, I shall return. It is unfortunate that I didn’t indulge in some of the cuisine, perhaps next time. Wide assortment of fermented beverages for the palate of any connoisseur, and those dedicated to a quaffing fest for the evening!!!! No thumbs down on this experience!!!! Prost!
